It's understood gunmen in three vehicles tried to stop the cash truck by opening fire on the vehicle on the road. JOHANNESBURG Police are searching for a gang involved in an attempted cash-in-transit heist in Limpopo.It is understood that gunmen in three vehicles tried to stop the cash truck by opening fire on the vehicle on the road.Security guards driving the truck returned fire, wounding some of the suspects.The police's Moatshe Ngoepe says: We are calling out to all members of the community who might know the suspects or who can see the suspects coming to consult at any medical facility, because seemingly some of them were shot and injured. 